==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Covering
<hw>Cov"er*ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Anything which covers or
conceals, as a roof, a screen, a wrapper, clothing, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Noah removed the <qex>covering</qex> of the ark.</q> <rj><qau>Gen.
viii. 13.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They cause the naked to lodge without clothing, that they have no
<qex>covering</qex> in the cold.</q> <rj><qau>Job. xxiv.
7.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>covering</qex> over the well's mouth.</q> <rj><qau>2 Sam.
xvii. 19.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coverlet</ent>⟦br⟧
